      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6, boil a kettle, then take your<strong> chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into<strong> </strong>fries, then add to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and your <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crispy – these are your <strong>paprika fries</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2163.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2163.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2163.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2163.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2163.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the fries are cooking, add your <strong>ground cumin</strong>, <strong>dried oregano</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can’t handle the heat? Go easy!) and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>to a plate</p><p>Gently stir it all together – this is your <strong>spice mix</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>free</strong> <strong>range</strong> <strong>chicken breast portion[s]</strong> to the plate and turn several times until fully coated in the spice mix</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1592843145103-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1592843145103-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1592843145103-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1592843145103-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1592843145103-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>spiced</strong> <strong>chicken</strong> and cook for 3 min on each side or until browned</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1592843149033-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1592843149033-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1592843149033-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1592843149033-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1592843149033-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, dissolve your<strong> tomato paste</strong> in 200ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [275ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your<strong> tomato stock</strong></p><p>Grate your<strong> cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>mayo</strong> and<strong> white wine vinegar</strong> in a small bowl and set aside for later – this is your <strong>zingy mayo</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2163.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2163.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2163.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2163.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2163.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken has browned, add the <strong>tomato stock</strong> and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Tip: Flip the chicken occasionally to keep it moist!</p><p>Meanwhile, wash your<strong> lettuce</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper, remove 2 <strong>outer leaves </strong>per person and shred the <strong>inner core[s]</strong></p><p>Dice your<strong> tomato[es]</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1592843154843-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1592843154843-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1592843154843-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1592843154843-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1592843154843-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut your <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong> in half and add to a baking tray, cut-side up</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 3-4 min or until warmed through and slightly crispy</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4 or more? You may need to use 2 trays!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2163.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2163.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2163.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2163.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2163.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is cooked, transfer to a clean board and shred it apart, using two forks – this technique is known as ‘pulling’</p><p>Return the <strong>pulled chicken</strong> to the pan, season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and mix it all up until fully coated in the sauce</p><p>Return the pan to a medium heat, top the pulled chicken with the <strong>grated cheese</strong> and cook, covered, for 1 min further or until melted – this is your <strong>Mexican-style pulled free-range chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2163.-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2163.-step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2163.-step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2163.-step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2163.-step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To build your burger, fill the <strong>warmed ciabatta</strong> with a <strong>lettuce leaf</strong>, <strong>Mexican-style pulled free-range chicken</strong> and <strong>zingy mayo</strong> – this is your <strong>Mexican-style pulled free range chicken burger</strong></p><p>Serve the<strong> paprika fries</strong>, <strong>shredded lettuce </strong>and<strong> diced tomato </strong>to the side</p><p>Drizzle any<strong> remaining zingy mayo </strong>over the lettuce and tomato</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
